 To appoint such employees, agents and representatives as it may
deem necessary, and to determine compensation and to define the
duties of each;

 To keep minutes, books and records which will reflect all of the
acts and transactions of the committee and which shall be subject to
examination by the Secretary;

 To prepare periodic statements of the financial operations of the
committee and to make copies of each such statement available to
growers and handlers for examination at the office of the committee;

 To cause its books to be audited by a public accountant at least
once each fiscal year and at such times as the Secretary may
request;

Committee meetings may be assembled or held by telephone, video conference, or other means of communication. The committee may vote by telephone, facsimile, or other means of communication. Votes by members or alternates present at assembled meetings shall be cast in person. Votes by members or alternates participating by telephone or other means of communication shall be by roll call;
Provided,
That a video conference shall be considered an assembled meeting, and votes by those participating through video conference shall be considered as cast in person.
